## What is ΣBUS?

ΣBUS is not an agent framework. It is the **substrate beneath agents** — a universal event,
metadata, and interaction matrix that lets AI systems perceive, classify, reason over, and act
on sensors, GUIs, RF streams, autonomous subsystems, and other agents through one coherent model.

```
MCP  ──→  tools and resources
A2A  ──→  structured cross-framework task delegation
ΣBUS ──→  registers, normalises, routes, and preserves ALL actionable perception and state
```

ΣBUS sits **under** MCP and A2A, not beside them.

