## Core Concepts

### Path Naming
Every data item in ΣBUS is addressed by a fully-qualified hierarchical path:
```
{platform}.{domain}.{entity}.{attribute}

wibo835.nav.position.gps_primary.lat
wibo835.engine.port.temp_coolant
wibo835.agent.nav_agent.last_decision
wibo835.meta.stream.health
```

### ΣFrame
Every message in the system is a ΣFrame — a typed payload wrapped in a SemanticEnvelope:
```json
{
  "msg_id": "uuid-v4",
  "msg_type": "OBSERVATION",
  "sender": "agt-wibo835-nav-001",
  "subject": "wibo835.nav.position.gps_primary",
  "timestamp_us": 1716123456892000,
  "payload": { "lat": 51.9225, "lon": 4.4792, "fix_type": "3d" },
  "envelope": {
    "identity_trust": 0.98,
    "behavioral_trust": 0.94,
    "evidence_trust": 0.97,
    "authority_scope": ["wibo835.nav.*", "wibo835.meta.*"],
    "half_life_s": 2.0,
    "cross_validated": true,
    "path": ["gps_primary_antenna", "nmea_mux", "signalk_plugin"],
    "anomaly_score": 0.01,
    "retention": "voyage"
  },
  "signature": "base64:ed25519-signature"
}
```

### Four-Dimension Trust Model
```
identity_trust    — cryptographic PKI verification score (static at registration)
behavioral_trust  — rolling Brier-scored outcome history (updated per action)
evidence_trust    — per-message provenance chain quality (computed per ΣFrame)
authority_scope   — declared and enforced write boundaries (hard gate)

effective_trust(path) = 0 if path ∉ authority_scope
                      = identity_trust×0.25 + behavioral_trust×0.50 + evidence_trust×0.25
```

