## Design Principles

1. **Fail-safe over fail-smart.** Deterministic safety layers are never delegated to AI.
2. **Human authority is inalienable.** No agent-to-agent agreement can override it.
3. **Every decision is traceable.** The decision journal is load-bearing structure.
4. **Trust decays with age.** Stale data is not trusted. Half-lives are per data type.
5. **Metadata is richer than data.** The envelope carries more information than the payload.
6. **Offline sovereign.** The system must operate without any cloud dependency.

